title: Dr. Phil Meets with Schizophrenic 10-Year-Old | Dr. Phil
description:
Michael and Susan say when their daughter, Jani, was born, they immediately noticed that she wasnâ€™t like other children. They say as a newborn, Jani would sleep only three hours a day, and as she grew older, would see, hear and feel things that were not there. At 6 years old, Jani was diagnosed with early-onset schizophrenia. Now 10, Jani, who has tested with a genius IQ, spends up to 95 percent of her days in an imaginary world she calls Calalini, where more than 100 people and animals reside. Michael and Susan say Janiâ€™s imaginary friends bring her comfort but also encourage her to act out, often in violent and destructive ways. While medication regulates her explosive tendencies, Michael and Susan say they fear for her future. They share a candid look inside their life, including the toll schizophrenia has taken on their marriage. Plus, find out why they fear their second child, Bodhi, whom they say they had as a companion for Jani, may be showing signs of the illness. And, Dr. Phil spends the day with Jani. Learn what he uncovers about her secret world. Then, Ashley, 25, was diagnosed with schizophrenia as a child and says sheâ€™s now replaced her medication with dangerous street drugs. Can Dr. Phil get her on the road to recovery? (2311015)

title: Stories From The Border: Tom Homan | Incoming Border Czar | Ep. 278 | Dr. Phil Podcast
description:
Dr. Phil continues his conversation with Tom Homan, the newly appointed border czar under President Trump, about his extensive experience in law enforcement and immigration enforcement over three decades. They dive into the political motivations behind border policies, the operational control of cartels, and the multifaceted challenges to border security, including terrorism risks and the humanitarian plight of migrants. Homanâ€™s perspectivesâ€”to many, controversialâ€”connect deeply with his long-standing commitment to enforcing immigration laws, as well as his emotional investments in preventing human suffering. The discussion captures a complex narrative of national security, politics, and humanitarian ethics, contributing to ongoing debates around U.S. border policy and enforcement. Dr. Phil supports Homanâ€™s dedication, applauding his transparency and the humanitarian concern for those affected by illegal border crossings. Throughout, the emphasis remains on securing borders to protect American citizens and migrants from harm. Whether you agree with his methods or not, there's no denying that Tom is a key player in the ongoing debate over border security.

title: Dr Phil Show: (Pt. 5 of Bring Back My Child): Conclusion of Episode
description:
Part V of Dr. Phil Show with Austin family law attorney from Law Office of KG, PLLC, Kimberly Gruber, representing client, Cecilia, who went on the run with her child when the court refused to address her concern that the baby's father may be abusing the child. After visitation with the father, Cecilia recalls that the baby would be returned with red marks and bruises, and in utter terror.
Cecilia, despite a clean criminal record, was arrested and imprisoned for a year for criminal charges of child abduction, regardless of the fact that she was in constant communication with the baby's father through the entire trip. When Cecilia was released; she dealt with the effects of the civil violations as well--- which to date, have suppressed her visitation with the child to an hour of supervised visitation a month. 
As Cecilia is supporting her mother, she barely has enough money to pay for the supervision of the visitations, let alone an attorney. At the time of the show, Attorney Kimberly Gruber had advised Cecilia of her options, and Cecilia was trying to get a retainer together. At the present, Kimberly and Keith began their own firm, Law Office of KG, PLLC, and are now able to take Cecilia as a pro bono case.   Kimberly, Keith and Cecilia are working together to regain Cecilia's parental rights.

title: Did She Marry an Imposter? | FULL EPISODE | Dr. Phil
description:
After a whirlwind four-month romance last year, Sheri married her soon-to-be ex, Tim. She claims he told her he was a retired doctor, former professional hockey player, wealthy businessman and Canadian air force pilot. But one month after the wedding, Sheri says she grew suspicious that Tim was cheating -- and soon unraveled what she calls a web of lies. She claims she learned from a news story that Tim had previously operated a pain management clinic in Texas -- without a medical license and under a different name -- and spent one year in prison for stealing nearly $30,000 from the parent company that owned the clinic. How could she not have known about Timâ€™s past? In a â€˜Dr. Philâ€™ exclusive, Tim -- via satellite -- shares his side of the story for the first time, in an effort to clear his name. Why does he say the allegations are bogus? And, why is he unable to travel to Los Angeles for the show? Then, Timâ€™s former fiancÃ©e -- who claims she, too, was deceived by him -- makes a shocking revelation about her ex. Plus, what did the â€˜Dr. Philâ€™ staff find when they investigated Timâ€™s history? How will he react to the findings? (From Dr. Phil Season 12)

title: This Woman Provides An Update After Her Ex-Husband Was Convicted Of Killing Their Son
description:
Dr. Phil updates two crime stories. After 13-year-old Dylan Redwine disappeared in November 2012, his divorced parents, Elaine and Mark, and older brother, Cory, appeared on Dr.Phil trying to find answers. Almost 10 years later, Dylanâ€™s father, Mark Redwine - who sat on the stage and denied knowing anything about his sonâ€™s whereabouts â€“ was convicted of killing Dylan. Elaine and Cory update Dr. Phil on the details of the case since Mark was found guilty last fall and sentenced to 48 years in prison. Dr. Phil discusses how they can finally move on with their lives now that they have sought justice for Dylan. Then, hear from Cheryl, who appeared on Dr. Phil eight years ago, to find out what happened to her two grandchildren, 4-year-old Keira and 18-month-old Darby, who died just three months apart. She said she thought it was very suspicious and wanted answers. Today, Cheryl is still fighting for justice and says she will always be looking for the truth. Dr. Phil, as well as Elaine and Cory, offer words of encouragement and support. (20121)

description:

The story rocked their small Idaho town and left two families forever changed. Kandiâ€™s husband, Rob, who claimed he acted in self-defense, was convicted of second-degree murder and sentenced to 30 years in prison. For the first time since the trial four years ago, Ashlee and Kandi come face to face on Dr. Philâ€™s stage. What happened that fateful night? Kandi was the closest witness -- what does she remember? And, Ashlee says she had no idea Emmett was having an affair, but Kandi claims she wasnâ€™t his only extra-marital partner. Plus, Kandi claims Ashlee has tried to ruin her by smearing her name in books and blogs. How does Ashlee respond? And, hear Robâ€™s statement from behind bars. title: A Family Divided Over An Unsolved Murder | FULL EPISODE | Dr. Phil
description:
In August 2009, Pennyâ€™s 40-year-old sister, Shannon, a successful businesswoman, was found dead in her car, at the bottom of a cliff, in what authorities initially believed was a tragic accident but later ruled a homicide -- a case that remains unsolved. Emotions run high when Penny faces her father, Ted, for the first time in two years and drops a bombshell: She believes he hired a hitman to kill Shannon. Ted admits his relationship with Shannon was strained at the time, but he vehemently denies he had anything to do with her death. How will Ted react to Pennyâ€™s accusation? Tune in to watch the drama unfold as this father and daughter angrily level charges against each other -- can Penny and Ted find a way to repair their relationship, or have the accusations gone too far? (From Dr. Phil Season 13)

title: Judy Byington - Dr. Phil Show
description:
As the only known survivor-intended-victim of a human sacrificial ceremony, Jenny Hill is living proof that ritual abuse is, in fact, a reality. With great courage and in open defiance of her sadistic abusers, Jenny wishes her story told. The ending will shock you.

Referring to journals written throughout childhood, Jenny Hill and her multiple personalities document how as a five year-old, she overcomes trauma by turning to prayer while utilizing her alter states to compartmentalize abuse at the hands of a master mind-control programmer from Nazi Germany. After suffering deaths of a high school sweetheart, plus her only girlfriend, she somehow completes Army medic training, receives a nursing degree, prepares for a church mission and becomes a mother.

Simultaneously led by sex-addict Head Alter J.J., intrepid alters assume frequent control, engaging in larceny and prostitution. With her children, her lifeline, the increasingly desperate nurse escapes a drugged-out pimping husband, blacks out in a job interview, comes to nine days later as an inpatient headed for the Utah State Psychiatric Hospital and only then learns what her life has really been.

title: Dr. Phil and Dr. Oz Fight Scammers (Part 1)
description:

(ã£â—”â—¡â—”)ã£ðŸ”” Subscribe and "Ring the Bell" to get notified when we post new videos!

Dr. Phil teams up for the first time with bestselling author, heart surgeon, and Emmy Award-winning host of The Doctor Oz Show, Dr. Mehmet Oz, to take on and fight internet fraudsters who have stolen their names and likenesses to endorse CBD products. Dr. Phil and Dr. Oz work to get the word out that they have never endorsed or sold any CBD products. Both doctors talk with Dr. Salimpour Pedram at a Los Angeles laboratory where some of the falsely marketed products were tested â€“ what did those tests reveal? As part of their joint investigation, Dr. Phil and Dr. Oz also interview William Teller, an actor hired to pose as the owner of one CBD company â€“ and you wonâ€™t believe what they learn! Internet Scam Investigator Chris Durst discusses how she helped to locate William Teller. They also talk to two viewers who say they were scammed by fake endorsements ... and one of them wants to tell Dr. Phil why she blamed him! Retired FBI agent and Cybercrime Expert Scott Augenbaum offers advice to avoid scams and action tips for scam victims. Finally, meet Alex, who thought she got a new job but actually fell victim to an employment scam.

title: Thursday, April 29 on The Dr. Phil Show: Revenge Revisited
description:
We've all heard the saying, "Dont get mad, get even," but after watching this show, you may think twice before seeking vindication! When husband and wife Deborah and Todd on Dr. Phil, Deborah admitted to embellishing the truth to get revenge on Todd, which landed him in jail for almost a year. At that time, Todd vowed to get even. A few days after the show, he got his wish, and what has happened since seems like a made-for-TV movie! In a strange twist of events, Deborah received a text message stating that Todd had died. But two weeks later, she received a phone call from him! Todd joins the show to explain his side of the story. Did he fake his own death, or was it all a big misunderstanding? When Dr. Phil drills down, will the truth finally come out? And, the couple didn't take Dr. Phil's advice after the previous show, but will they now? You won't believe the twists and turns in this story of revenge! description:
Dr. Phil is an American talk show created by Oprah Winfrey and the host Phil McGraw. After McGraw's success with his segments on The Oprah Winfrey Show, Dr. Phil debuted on September 16, 2002. On both shows McGraw offers advice in the form of "life strategies" from his life experience as a clinical and forensic psychologist.[3] The show is in syndication throughout the United States and a number of other countries. The executive producers are Phil McGraw and showrunner Oprah Winfrey. It is a production of Peteski Productions and distributed by CBS Media Ventures. Harpo Productions co-produced the series until 2010, with Paramount Domestic Television and its successor, CBS Paramount Domestic Television, serving as secondary co-producers until 2007. It was originally distributed by King World Productions.

The program is recorded before a live studio audience in Stage 29 on the Paramount Pictures lot in Hollywood, California. It is recorded from August through to May with a break in December for the holiday season. On October 25, 2018, it was announced that Dr. Phil had been renewed for four additional seasons, taking the show to May 2023, or the end of its 21st season.

title: Dr Phil Show 2022  _ I Hate My Daughter in Law
description:
Dr. Phil is an American talk show created by Oprah Winfrey and the host Phil McGraw. After McGraw's success with his segments on The Oprah Winfrey Show, Dr. Phil debuted on September 16, 2002. On both shows McGraw offers advice in the form of "life strategies" from his life experience as a clinical and forensic psychologist.[3] The show is in syndication throughout the United States and a number of other countries. Occasional prime time specials have aired on CBS. The program has been nominated for a Daytime Emmy Award every year since 2004.

The executive producers are Phil McGraw and showrunner Oprah Winfrey. It is a production of Peteski Productions and distributed by CBS Media Ventures. Harpo Productions co-produced the series until 2010, with Paramount Domestic Television and its successor, CBS Paramount Domestic Television, serving as secondary co-producers until 2007. It was originally distributed by King World Productions.

The program is recorded before a live studio audience in Stage 29 on the Paramount Pictures lot in Hollywood, California. It is recorded from August through to May with a break in December for the holiday season. On October 25, 2018, it was announced that Dr. Phil had been renewed for four additional seasons, taking the show to May 2023, or the end of its 21st season.

Genre Talk show

Oprah Winfrey

title: ðŸ†ðŸŒ³ Dr Phil Show 2022 ðŸ†ðŸŒ³ Three Sisters Finally Confront Their Stepfather Polygraph Result
description:
Dr. Phil is an American talk show created by Oprah Winfrey and the host Phil McGraw. After McGraw's success with his segments on The Oprah Winfrey Show, Dr. Phil debuted on September 16, 2002. On both shows McGraw offers advice in the form of "life strategies" from his life experience as a clinical and forensic psychologist.[3] The show is in syndication throughout the United States and a number of other countries. Occasional prime time specials have aired on CBS. The program has been nominated for a Daytime Emmy Award every year since 2004.

The executive producers are Phil McGraw and showrunner Oprah Winfrey. It is a production of Peteski Productions and distributed by CBS Media Ventures. Harpo Productions co-produced the series until 2010, with Paramount Domestic Television and its successor, CBS Paramount Domestic Television, serving as secondary co-producers until 2007. It was originally distributed by King World Productions.

The program is recorded before a live studio audience in Stage 29 on the Paramount Pictures lot in Hollywood, California. It is recorded from August through to May with a break in December for the holiday season. On October 25, 2018, it was announced that Dr. Phil had been renewed for four additional seasons, taking the show to May 2023, or the end of its 21st season.

PodBean

Advising Teresa that â€œQuitting cold-turkey is not an option right now,â€ because it would be too risky for both her and her unborn child, OB-GYN Dr. ThaÃ¯s Aliabadi offered to help Teresa through the final weeks of her pregnancy with specialized treatment and prenatal care.

title: ðŸ†ðŸŒ³ Dr Phil Show 2022 ðŸ†ðŸŒ³ My Tourette's Made Me Viral
description:
Dr. Phil is an American talk show created by Oprah Winfrey and the host Phil McGraw. After McGraw's success with his segments on The Oprah Winfrey Show, Dr. Phil debuted on September 16, 2002. On both shows McGraw offers advice in the form of "life strategies" from his life experience as a clinical and forensic psychologist.[3] The show is in syndication throughout the United States and a number of other countries. Occasional prime time specials have aired on CBS. The program has been nominated for a Daytime Emmy Award every year since 2004.

The executive producers are Phil McGraw and showrunner Oprah Winfrey. It is a production of Peteski Productions and distributed by CBS Media Ventures. Harpo Productions co-produced the series until 2010, with Paramount Domestic Television and its successor, CBS Paramount Domestic Television, serving as secondary co-producers until 2007. It was originally distributed by King World Productions.

The program is recorded before a live studio audience in Stage 29 on the Paramount Pictures lot in Hollywood, California. It is recorded from August through to May with a break in December for the holiday season. On October 25, 2018, it was announced that Dr. Phil had been renewed for four additional seasons, taking the show to May 2023, or the end of its 21st season.

Dr. Phil is an American talk show created by Oprah Winfrey and the host Phil McGraw. After McGraw's success with his segments on The Oprah Winfrey Show, Dr. Phil debuted on September 16, 2002. On both shows McGraw offers advice in the form of "life strategies" from his life experience as a clinical and forensic psychologist.[3] The show is in syndication throughout the United States and a number of other countries. Occasional prime time specials have aired on CBS. The program has been nominated for a Daytime Emmy Award every year since 2004.

The executive producers are Phil McGraw and showrunner Oprah Winfrey. It is a production of Peteski Productions and distributed by CBS Media Ventures. Harpo Productions co-produced the series until 2010, with Paramount Domestic Television and its successor, CBS Paramount Domestic Television, serving as secondary co-producers until 2007. It was originally distributed by King World Productions.

The program is recorded before a live studio audience in Stage 29 on the Paramount Pictures lot in Hollywood, California. It is recorded from August through to May with a break in December for the holiday season. On October 25, 2018, it was announced that Dr. Phil had been renewed for four additional seasons, taking the show to May 2023, or the end of its 21st season.

description:
Dr. Phil is an American talk show created by Oprah Winfrey and the host Phil McGraw. After McGraw's success with his segments on The Oprah Winfrey Show, Dr. Phil debuted on September 16, 2002. On both shows McGraw offers advice in the form of "life strategies" from his life experience as a clinical and forensic psychologist.[3] The show is in syndication throughout the United States and a number of other countries. Occasional prime time specials have aired on CBS. The program has been nominated for a Daytime Emmy Award every year since 2004.

The executive producers are Phil McGraw and showrunner Oprah Winfrey. It is a production of Peteski Productions and distributed by CBS Media Ventures. Harpo Productions co-produced the series until 2010, with Paramount Domestic Television and its successor, CBS Paramount Domestic Television, serving as secondary co-producers until 2007. It was originally distributed by King World Productions.

The program is recorded before a live studio audience in Stage 29 on the Paramount Pictures lot in Hollywood, California. It is recorded from August through to May with a break in December for the holiday season. On October 25, 2018, it was announced that Dr. Phil had been renewed for four additional seasons, taking the show to May 2023, or the end of its 21st season.

Genre Talk show

title: Dr. Phil Show Patient Testimonial | Top Beverly Hills Dentist
description:
A guest for the Dr. Phil show had a tooth missing and did not want to go on TV. Dr. Phil recommended and referred the guest to Dr. Joseph Goodman. The guest shares his experience with having his tooth replaced and how pleased he was with Dr. Goodman. He also thanks Dr. Phil for referring him to his personal dentist. 

Dr. Joseph Goodman helps celebrities, sports stars, beauty pageant contestants, royalty, and everyday people restore their smiles. Dr. Goodman has been a guest on The Doctors, Dr. Phil, and KTLA5.

Dr. Goodman has experience in prosthodontics, which is complex restorative, implant, and reconstructive dentistry. Before becoming a top cosmetic dentist in Beverly Hills, Dr. Goodman received training in all areas of modern dentistry. 

He worked for several years in Germany, pursuing his interest in prosthodontics and reconstructive dentistry before moving to Los Angeles in 1988. Today, he continues to travel around the world to help give people the beautiful smiles they deserve.

For further information about Dr. Goodman and his Top Beverly Hills Dentist practice, please feel free to visit our official website at https://www.topbeverlyhillsdentist.com/ or contact us at (424) 344-4597 today!
